 <br> 
 Steps;
 <br>
(i)	Add power (index) to each digit in a number from RHS to LHS e.g.
<br>
<strong>4 3 2 1 0</strong>
<br>
2 5 0 2 4 --------------- Number
<br>
<strong>Where;</strong> 4, 3, 2, 1, 0 are the powers
<br>
(ii)	Use each digit in the number to multiply the given or desired number base and its corresponding power, then add to one another.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
Expand the following (i) 25024<sub>6</sub> (ii) 10110<sub>2</sub> (iii) 4102<sub>5</sub> (iv) 2389<sub>10</sub> in powers of their bases.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
<strong>Note:</strong> any number raised to power of zero is <strong>1.</strong>
